results.title: Heart filled buffet runner. Red hearts and love lines on cream front. Red geometric back. Quilted center with thin batting.
results.description:
14.5" X 42.5" table, buffet, bed or desk runner is reversible if you don't mind hearts running wild in your maze. 

This project started out with soft cream cotton fabric that was covered with hearts and a sturdy cream and red "duck" (canvas) geometric back.  When the right sides were sewn together (outside inside) and then turned right side out, we suddenly were dealing with tooo tooooo many spots (hearts). 

Right then and there our eyesight needed to be saved.  The fix was a 6.5" center rectangle of cream fabric with repeating red "live laugh love" script.  

Of course you could see the background hearts through it. To fix that we chose a layer of thin white batting, which was needed only in the center strip.  THAT required quilting to hold the layers all together. 

Subsequently machine quilted small heart borders went on.  Followed by Red Work hearts along the center strip.  Getting totally carried away, purchased red hearts were appliqued to add spice. Not to let a good thing be done, four red heart buttons finish each corner. The eye problem went away and a bit more practice was had what with the free motion curves quilted in. 

The thicker center strip and heavy back will help protect your surfaces. If you enjoy the bright Valentine red and warm sentiments, this one is for you.  If you wanted plain and simple, sorry this ended up toooo HAPPY!  Somebody's gotta luv it besides us!  (And somebody needs to go upstairs and put the iron to work on the wrinkles.)
